      • AdditionalPrimaryABContactSearchCriteria

        @Deprecated
public static final ListParameterKey AdditionalPrimaryABContactSearchCriteria
        Deprecated. (Since 8.0.0) This parameter is no longer used in the code and was removed from config.xml.
        Names (comma separated) of fields to add to the list of primary search criteria. I.e. fields on ABContactSearchCriteria that would be searchable even without specifying any other criterion. Remember to add the appropriate indexes to the ABContact table, and to update the MinimumSearchCriteria display properties

      • MaxContactSearchResults

        public static final IntegerParameterKey MaxContactSearchResults
        The max number of contact search results to display in the UI *

      • MaxDuplicateContactsFinderWorkQueueResults

        public static final IntegerParameterKey MaxDuplicateContactsFinderWorkQueueResults
        The max number of duplicate contacts to be registered as duplicates by the DuplicateContactsFinderWorkQueue. If more duplicates are found for a given contact the DuplicateContactsFinderWorkQueue will not register any of the duplicates for that contact but instead log the ABUID.

      • DuplicateContactsEarliestModificationDate

        public static final DateTimeParameterKey DuplicateContactsEarliestModificationDate
        The duplicate contacts batch process acts on contacts created or modified after the last time it was run AND after the date specified by this parameter. This makes it possible to avoid processing every contact in the database the first time the batch process run. For example, if contacts are imported into the database on 8/21/2011 and this parameter is set to "08/22/2011 12:00 AM", those contacts will not be processed by the batch process unless they're later modified. Expected format: mm/dd/yyyy hh:mm am

      • DuplicateContactsWideSearch

        public static final BooleanParameterKey DuplicateContactsWideSearch
        Indicates whether the search for duplicate contacts should widen and not use subtype specific logic. Defaults to true.

      • MaxNumberServicesInSearchQuery

        public static final IntegerParameterKey MaxNumberServicesInSearchQuery
        The maximum number of services allowed in a contact search query. This is limited by the underlying database handling of IN clauses.

      • MaxDiffDisplaysInCache

        public static final IntegerParameterKey MaxDiffDisplaysInCache
        The max number of PendingChange DiffDisplays to store in the cache. Default is 60

      • DiffDisplaysCacheTimeoutInMinutes

        public static final IntegerParameterKey DiffDisplaysCacheTimeoutInMinutes
        The amount of time, in minutes since last access, that PendingChange DiffDisplays should be maintained in the PendingChange DiffDisplay cache. Default is 10 minutes
